<item>
 <title>Department of Energy Cites URS -Washington Division for Worker Safety Violations</title>
 <link>https://energy.gov/articles/department-energy-cites-urs-washington-division-worker-safety-violations</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div  property=&quot;content:encoded&quot; class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;WASHINGTON, D.C. – The U.S. Department of Energy (DOE) has issued a Preliminary Notice of Violation (PNOV) to URS -Washington Division (URS-WD) based on an investigation of an October 2010 incident at the DOE Idaho Site.  The PNOV cites URS-WD with two violations of the Department’s worker safety and health regulations associated with a hoisting incident that occurred when a telescopic hydraulic gantry system (THGS) tipped while lifting a 7,800 pound shield plug at the Sodium Bearing Waste Treatment Project (SBWTP).  The Department has proposed a $150,000 civil penalty.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
 <pubDate>Tue, 04 Oct 2011 13:53:00 +0000</pubDate>
 <dc:creator />
 <guid isPermaLink="false">305821 at https://energy.gov</guid>
